```julia
function keep_only_names(words::Vector{String})
    return filter(word -> startswith(word, uppercasefirst(word)), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` built-in function to retain only those strings that start with a capital letter when compared to their own first character converted to upper case. The `startswith` function is used to check if the word starts with the specified substring (which in this case is the same word but with the first character uppercased).
